text = "you know what they call a quarter pounder with cheese in france. they dont call it a quarter pounder. what do they call it. they call it a royal with cheese. royal with cheese. thats because of the metric system. they wouldnt know what the hell a quarter pound is. they dont even use that system over there. so they just go with something that makes sense to them. and it sounds a little fancier too. and the other guy is like what about a big mac. do they call it something different. and yeah they probably do. they just rename everything so it fits better with how they talk over there. its not the same language so the food ends up sounding different even though its basically the same thing."

